# WARDEN Project - Issue Resolution Summary

## Resolved Issues

**1. Fragmented AI Model (Responder & Staff Desktop Apps)**
- *Problem*: The `gemma-4-e2b.gguf` model file is fragmented into multiple `.part` files in the repository due to size constraints. The Tauri apps expect a unified file to run.
- *Resolution*: I updated the Rust setup logic in both `WARDEN/Responder Desktop App/src-tauri/src/main.rs` and `WARDEN/Staff Desktop App/app/src-tauri/src/main.rs`. Now, when the apps launch, they automatically check if the unified `.gguf` file exists. If it's missing but the `.part` files are present, the Rust backend programmatically streams and assembles the parts into the unified `gemma-4-e2b.gguf` file locally. This entirely eliminates the need for users to manually run the `rejoin_model.ps1` script!

**2. Hardcoded Cloud Endpoints (Warden Android App)**
- *Problem*: The `BASE_URL` in `com.jdcoders.crisisconnect.services.ApiConfig` was hardcoded to a Google Cloud Run instance instead of local IP routing for development.
- *Resolution*: I updated the `BASE_URL` in `WARDEN/Warden Android App/app/src/main/java/com/jdcoders/crisisconnect/services/ApiConfig.kt` from `https://warden-backend-774533752332.us-central1.run.app` to `http://10.0.2.2:8000`. This enables the Android app (when running in an Emulator) to correctly map to the host machine's local standalone backend, honoring the local-first rules.

**3. Undocumented Component (Website)**
- *Problem*: The `Website` directory (React 19 / Vite / Tailwind) was not mentioned in any of the core documentation (`PRD.md`, `TRD.md`, `Implementation.md`), leaving its purpose undefined within the ecosystem.
- *Resolution*: I updated the documentation to officially integrate the Website component into the WARDEN ecosystem. 
  - In `PRD.md`, I added it to the System Architecture section as the public-facing informational portal.
  - In `TRD.md`, I included it in the Technology Stack under a new `2.5 Public Website` section.
  - In `Implementation.md`, I documented it under `2.6 Public Website (Vite/React)` outlining its core modules (Landing Page and App Distribution links).

## Unresolved Issues

**4. Missing Executable (`llama-server.exe`) (Responder & Staff Desktop Apps)**
- *Problem*: The Rust setup functions explicitly try to spawn `binaries/llama-server.exe` to run the Gemma AI model, but the executable does not exist in the repository for either application.
- *Why I couldn't resolve it*: The `llama-server.exe` file is physically missing from the codebase. Furthermore, there are no download scripts, URLs, or specific version requirements documented in the repository `README.md` or anywhere else that would allow me to securely fetch or build the exact version of the executable required by WARDEN.
- *Recommended Action*: Please manually place the appropriate `llama-server.exe` inside the `src-tauri/binaries` directory for both apps, or provide a URL/script from which the build pipeline can fetch the executable automatically.
